OSOGBO – In a bid to resolve the current feud between Governor Adegboyega Oyetola of Osun State and his predecessor in office, now Minister of Interior, Ogbeni Rauf Aregbesola, the National Reconciliation Committee of the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC) set up to look into the crisis have arrived the state. The committee arrived Osogbo, Osun State Capital on Saturday in the morning and went straight to the Oke Fia Government House where the team met with Governor Oyetola and members of his camp. Led by its Chairman, Senator Adamu Abdullahi, the committee on arrival went into a close door meeting with the Governor and his team which include factional State Chairman of the party, Prince Gboyega Famodun, Special Adviser to Governor Oyetola on political matters, Hon. Sunday Akere, Deputy Chief of Staff, Hon. Binuyo, Hon. Debo Badru, Commissioner for Information, Funke Egbemode among others. Aftermath Of Abia APC Chairman’s Death, Ex-bank Chief Emerges… Fayemi Expresses Fresh Concern Over Assaults On Uniformed Men In… As at the time of filling this report, the committee was still holding meeting with Oyetola led group of the party while the committee is scheduled to hold another meeting with Aregbesola led Faction by 4.30pm at Aenon Suit located very close to the government house in Osogbo. Expected to attend the meeting include Adebiyi Adelowo, Chairman of TOP, Hon. Rasaq Salinsile, Chairman of the Aregbesola led Faction, Biodun Agboola among other. The crisis between Aregbesola and Oyetola has polarised the party in the state into two factions. No indication that Ogbeni Rauf Aregbesola would attend the meeting as there was no signal that he would be coming to the state for the meeting. But leadership of The TOP as well as Party executive under his camp have mobilised themselves for the meeting.